Crew members slightly randomise their laser shoot position on whether
they're attacking another crew member (from any ship of any race etc), or
anything else (eg locked doors). So doors always get laser-ed at the same position.
This is defined by CrewTarget::ExactTarget.

Damage is calculated (in CrewAnimation::OnUpdate, setting fDamageDone for punches,
and in CrewAnimation::OnUpdateEffects for laser shots) as:

  3.0 <= damage <= 7.0

This the base damage, before skill, race, and mind control bonuses are accounted for:

  final_damage = skill_mult * damage_mult * mindControl_mult * damage

(This is calculated in CrewMember::OnLoop)

When two crew members are punching each other, damage is done randomly between every 500ms-650ms, and then
an equal duration is spent letting the punch animation finish, so a full cycle is 1000ms-1300ms.
When a crew member is shooting another crew member, damage is done randomly between every 1000ms-1300ms.


Player animations:
CrewAnimation.anims is vector<vector<Animation>>, and means anims[direction][type]
direction:
* 0=down
* 1=right
* 2=up
* 3=left
type (from strings in CrewAnimation::OnInit):
* 0=walk
* 1=punch
* 2=repair (omnidirectional - all directions give the same image)
* 3=death
* 4=fire (as in firefighting - as compared to 'shoot')
* 5 - not defined
* 6=teleport (omnidirectional)
* 7=shoot
* 8=type
* 9=portrait (omnidirectional)
